LINE.Text: Physical, verbal, or psychological attacks or intimidation against a
person who cannot properly defend himself or herself. It includes two
key components: 1. Repeated harmful acts 2. Imbalance of power
HITTING, THREATENING INTIMIDATING, MALICIOUSLY TEASING AND TAUNTING,
NAME-CALLING, MAKING SEXUAL REMARKS, AND STEALING OR DAMAGING
BELONGINGS OR MORE SUBTLE, INDIRECT ATTACKS (SUCH AS SPREADING RUMORS
OR ENCOURAGING OTHERS TO REJECT OR EXCLUDE SOMEONE).
MORE YOUTH VIOLENCE OCCURS ON SCHOOL GROUNDS AS OPPOSED TO ON THE WAY TO SCHOOL
